{"type":"text","timestamp":1780728948019,"sessionID":"ses_1644b0d28ffeWU39CSDzij0Glk","part":{"id":"prt_e9bb75853001aKMKFEIxVIOgRG","messageID":"msg_e9bb7385d001B7ch01Flt7BwDU","sessionID":"ses_1644b0d28ffeWU39CSDzij0Glk","type":"text","text":"One correction emerged: `memory_soft_delete` itself is not strictly idempotent because a repeat call rewrites `deleted_at` to `now()`, extending the grace window. The purge and audit/fanout paths are idempotent/sticky, but the soft-delete primitive is weaker.","time":{"start":1780728944723,"end":1780728948009},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0291cfc200ee9c3e016a23c470b8548191b7405e0d662dd2de","phase":"commentary"}}}}
